    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Founded by Canandaigua banker Henry Gibson, the hamlet grew in the 1820s when he purchased canal frontage to create a port.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        23,
        24
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.visitfingerlakes.com/plan-your-trip/ontario-county-ny/hopewell-seneca-gorham/historic-port-gibson/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "In its heyday, Port Gibson hosted a malt house, planing mill, fruit‑drying facilities, and warehouses that served Erie Canal trade.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        24
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.visitfingerlakes.com/plan-your-trip/ontario-county-ny/hopewell-seneca-gorham/historic-port-gibson/"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The Erie Canal borders Port Gibson’s northern edge, and New York State Route 31 follows the waterway through the community.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        15,
        16
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Port_Gibson%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "Small‑boat access on the canal lets kayakers launch from Port Gibson and enjoy scenic views of rolling farmlands.",
